                        <h2>Over the Counter Methods</h2>

                        <h3>Whitening Toothpaste</h3>
                        <p>
                            Surface stains caused by coffee or cigarettes (or both!) can be removed with whitening toothpaste. This is 
                            partially down to the presence of blue covarine, a chemical that clings to the teeth and tones down the 
                            yellow hues you may have. Use whitening toothpaste twice a day and you&rsquo;ll begin to see effects in two 
                            to six weeks (unless it has blue covarine in which case you&rsquo;ll notice effects very rapidly). Do be 
                            aware, however, that whitening toothpaste is very surface in its approach. It won&rsquo;t alter the natural 
                            tooth color nor affect a stain that is inherently deeper than the surface.
                        </p>

                        <h3>Whitening Strips</h3>
                        <p>
                            These are regarded as mostly safe and often work even better than whitening toothpaste as they bleach your 
                            teeth. Again, be sure to follow the directions.
                        </p>

